On Wednesday, Prague&#39;s public transport will also use a chip for the first time
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will go down in the history of the Prague Transport Company as the date when the first passengers who will have an electronic coupon in their pocket instead of a paper ticket will board the metro, trams and buses.
At the moment, approximately one hundred thousand people who own an Opencard chip card can purchase it.
Passengers can buy a 30-day, 90-day and annual coupon (which will be valid from January 1, 2009) and have it uploaded to their chip card at the info centers and workplaces of the Transport Company in the metro stations Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Paradise Garden, Kačerov and Luka.
