This could be deals on the capital market or part of them.
However, the discussions have only just begun, financiers point out.
Deka-Bank, which with its 3,000 employees is one of the most important employers on the financial market in Frankfurt, is not the first to be talked about in connection with consolidation in the savings sector.
In 2003, it seemed for a while that Deka-Bank might merge with Landesbank Rheinland-Pfalz and Helaba bank.
In the end, nothing came of this trio.
