The two remaining banking houses did not merge in this way either.
Instead, Landesbank Rheinland-Pfalz acquired Landesbank Baden-Württemberg of Stuttgart.
Despite this, there were repeated speculations about the connection of Deka-Bank with regional banks.
Recently, however, Günther Merl, the chairman of the board of directors of Helaba bank, commented negatively on speculations about the merger of his financial house with others.
However, regardless of this, there seems to be a growing belief that bringing the various public sector banking houses closer together is a must.
Now, after the elections to the state assembly in Bavaria, the merger of BayernLB with Landesbank Baden-Württemberg could be the first to begin to take shape.
This is not exactly good news for Helaba.
If the pressure for further mergers should increase, it gradually loses possible partners for such a connection.
In the south, it would only play second fiddle, despite the fact that it has so far faced the financial crisis significantly better than the banking houses in Munich and Stuttgart.
At the beginning of the year, the connection with WestLB was banned by the Association of Savings and Savings Banks Hessen-Thüringen, which has an eighty-five percent stake in Helab.
Nord LB would be considered at most.
But geostrategic considerations of this kind are only one side of the problem.
On the other hand, it is a question of how well the business models of the individual institutions harmonize with each other.
In June, Merl stated that the German Association of Savings and Giro Banks has not yet answered the crucial question of what business model should be used to ensure the future competitiveness of regional banks.
Everything could also end with the dissolution of WestLB, which of course no one in this institution wants.
That is why the letter from the local board of directors also mentions that they are trying to find a &quot;comprehensive solution&quot; for the entire banking house.
Time will tell whether and how it will be possible to connect the individual components with Deka-Bank.
