Dark matter affects the flight of space probes
For years, scientists have been puzzled by one mysterious phenomenon: dark matter affects the speed of space probes during the so-called swing-by maneuver (gravitational slingshot).
Experts fear that Albert Einstein&#39;s general theory of relativity might not be completely correct.
