It was spoken of as a perfect race, and in my judgment was the worst I have ever been on.
Such a bunch of nonsense that immediately, if it came to the evaluation and I was the examiner, it would be clearly insufficient.
But let&#39;s look at it from the beginning, one by one.
The nonsense starts with picking up the race number, which requires you to set off early.
That doesn&#39;t seem bad to me, but if you go there, let them give you everything (including a chip to prevent overcrowding of the track).
But not.
Here one had to pick up a number first (the first nonsense, going there only for that) and (after standing in the appropriate queue) - what a surprise! - they only had a size S t-shirt (another nonsense, because I need an XL size).
Where do we live?
Because of the crisis, they decided to buy only small t-shirts because it&#39;s less fabric and they&#39;re cheaper?
