Domestic sales prices in industry increased by 0.1 percent compared to the previous month in August 2008, and by 12.9 percent compared to August 2007, the Central Statistical Office announced.
Export sales prices in industry were higher by 1.1 percent compared to July 2008, and decreased by 3.9 percent year-on-year.
Production prices in industry, as the cause of changes in domestic and export prices, were higher by 0.7 percent compared to the previous month, and rose by 3.2 percent year-on-year.
Domestic sales prices in industry rose only minimally, by 0.1 percent, compared to the previous month.
Domestic sales prices in manufacturing industries also increased slightly, by 0.1 percent, compared to July.
