Prices in the production and distribution of electricity, gas and water exceeded the prices of the previous year by 18.7 percent.
From the point of view of division according to the focus of the sector, in August domestic sales showed the highest monthly price increase (0.7 percent) in sectors involved in the production of tangible assets.
In sectors producing consumer goods, prices rose by 0.3 percent, in energy processing and further processing sectors, prices did not change compared to the previous month.
The largest price increase compared to the same month of the previous year was observed in August 2008 in the energy processing and further processing industries (16.8 percent).
In sectors producing consumer goods, we measured a price increase of 6.8 percent, while for tangible assets, on the other hand, prices fell by 1.4 percent.
Export sales prices of industrial products measured in forints increased by 1.1 percent in August compared to the previous month, and decreased by 3.9 percent in the twelve-month comparison.
Within one month, our domestic currency weakened by 1.7 percent against the euro, then by 7.1 percent against the dollar, compared to August 2007 it strengthened against the euro by 7.5 percent and against the dollar by 15.9 percent .
